resource.title: Treatment plan for pancreatic adenocarcinoma
resource.description: Comprehensive treatment plan including Surgery, Chemotherapy, Radiotherapy

resource.conclusion: Patient shows improving status for pancreatic adenocarcinoma. Sarita Nguyen, a 56-year-old Asian female diagnosed with Stage IV pancreatic adenocarcinoma, underwent pancreatectomy followed by six cycles of chemotherapy and 15 sessions of radiotherapy. She is currently in the follow-up phase undergoing regular assessments and treatments to manage her condition.
